<paragraph id="4529E750B479C250EFA6FCFFFECE5803" blockId="1.[151,981,795,854]" box="[151,281,830,854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
(
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EFAEFCFFFEC75803" box="[159,272,830,854]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStart-1="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId-0="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox-0="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetBox-1="[169,1428,204,1765]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[158,1428,193,1770]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 8 – 12. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Female paratype: 8, abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; 9, pygofer, lateral view; 10, internal abdominal sternite VIII, dorsal view; 11, first valvula of ovipositor, apical portion and dorsal sculpturing in detail, lateral view; 12, second valvula of ovipositor, dorsal and apical portions in detail, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/216428/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Figs 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EFE6FCFFFEC75803" box="[215,272,830,854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="6.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="1.0">1–12</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4529E750B479C250EFA6FC47FBEF58CB" blockId="1.[151,1437,902,2006]" box="[151,1080,902,927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Length. Male 
<typeStatus id="9A2D59F2B479C250EE05FC47FE4E58CB" box="[308,409,902,926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<quantity id="826E4AB5B479C250EE95FC47FE2958CB" box="[420,510,902,926]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
; male 
<typeStatus id="9A2D59F2B479C250ED77FC46FD7E58CA" box="[582,681,903,927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">paratype</typeStatus>
, 
<quantity id="826E4AB5B479C250ED84FC47FCD958CB" box="[693,782,902,926]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="9.9">9.9 mm</quantity>
; female 
<typeStatus id="9A2D59F2B479C250EC5DFC46FC1858CA" box="[876,975,903,927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">paratype</typeStatus>
, 
<quantity id="826E4AB5B479C250ECEBFC47FBE358CB" box="[986,1076,902,926]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="9.8">9.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4529E750B479C250EFF6FC6BFC745FCF" blockId="1.[151,1437,902,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Male 
<typeStatus id="9A2D59F2B479C250EE3BFC6BFEA75897" box="[266,368,938,962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">holotype</typeStatus>
. Head and thorax. Head (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EDA6FC6BFCD75897" box="[663,768,938,962]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin slightly angled; crown with median length 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EFD7FC0FFF2458B3" box="[230,243,974,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EFCDFC0FFEC058B3" box="[252,279,974,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="10.0">10</number>
interocular width and 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250ED2DFC0FFDF158B3" box="[540,550,974,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250ED00FC0FFD9658B3" box="[561,577,974,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="2.0">2</number>
transocular width, surface slightly concave medially; ocelli located on line between anterior eye angles, each ocellus slightly closer to median line of crown than to adjacent anterior eye angle; frons with muscle impressions distinct. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EC2DFBD7FCA85F7B" box="[796,895,1046,1070]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with width slightly less than transocular width; lateral margins convergent anteriorly; dorsopleural carina complete. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EB03FBFBFB405F07" box="[1074,1175,1082,1106]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) slightly striate behind scutoscutellar suture. 
<collectingCountry id="3D81A7C0B479C250EEBAFB9FFE145F23" box="[395,451,1118,1142]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Hind</collectingCountry>
legs with femoral setal formula 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EC1FFB9FFCE85F23" box="[814,831,1118,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="2.0">2</number>
:0:0. Remaining morphological characteristics of head and thorax as in the generic description of Young (
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EDFCFB43FCDD5FCF" box="[717,778,1154,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1977.0">1977</number>
: 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EC24FB43FC4F5FCF" box="[789,920,1154,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1085.0" valueMax="1086.0" valueMin="1084.0">
<date id="3128C190B479C250EC24FB43FC4F5FCF" box="[789,920,1154,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1084" valueMax="1086">1084–1086</date>
</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4529E750B479C250EFF6FB67FAED5D1F" blockId="1.[151,1437,902,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Male genitalia. Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EED2FB67FD9C5FEB" box="[483,587,1190,1214]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) moderately produced posteriorly in lateral view; basiventral portion with conspicuous cleft; apical portion strongly narrowed; disc with numerous short macrosetae grouped on midventral portion, extending sparsely along ventral margin to apex, numerous short sparse microsetae on ventral and apical portions; dorsoapical margin with inner unciform process, long and medially turned. Valve (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EBFFFAD3FAC25E7F" box="[1230,1301,1298,1322]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EA36FAD3FAC25E7F" box="[1287,1301,1298,1322]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad and subpentagonal; posterior margin angled, well produced. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250ECDFFAF7FBE45E1B" box="[1006,1075,1334,1358]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EB14FAF7FBE45E1B" box="[1061,1075,1334,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) triangular; dorsal surface with sclerotized tubercle-like process on basal half, on which apical portions of styles rest, and with slight curved carina mostly on apical half. Styles (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EEDFFABFFDE35EC3" box="[494,564,1406,1430]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250ED14FABFFDE35EC3" box="[549,564,1406,1430]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) extending posteriorly slightly farther than connective apex; outer preapical portion with long sparse setae; apical portion elongate, directed outward. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EBB7FA63FB195EEF" box="[1158,1230,1442,1466]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EB8EFA63FB195EEF" box="[1215,1230,1442,1466]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) with basiventral unpaired process; process, in lateral view, approximately twice longer than broad, with anterior margin concave and apex produced, acute, and curved anteriorly; shaft short and curved ventrally, with dorsal preapical rounded lobe; apex narrowly rounded; gonopore apical; dorsal apodemes long and strongly curved posteriorly. Remaining morphological characteristics of male genitalia as in the generic description of Young (
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EB55F9F3FB765D1F" box="[1124,1185,1586,1610]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1977.0">1977</number>
: 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EB9AF9F3FAF85D1F" box="[1195,1327,1586,1610]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1085.0" valueMax="1086.0" valueMin="1084.0">
<date id="3128C190B479C250EB9AF9F3FAF85D1F" box="[1195,1327,1586,1610]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1084" valueMax="1086">1084–1086</date>
</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4529E750B479C253EFF6F997FAFE5A6A" blockId="1.[151,1437,902,2006]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,644]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Color. Anterior dorsum (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EEEAF997FDE85D3B" box="[475,575,1622,1646]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with ground color yellow with dark brown maculae. Crown (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EBC6F997FA8C5D3B" box="[1271,1371,1622,1646]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with pair of anteromedian elongate dark brown maculae; pair of longitudinal dark brown stripes on antennal ledges; pale brown macula on apex of coronal suture; irregular dark brown maculae surrounding ocelli; posterior margin with pair of dark brown maculae behind ocellar maculae. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EC58F903FC185D8F" box="[873,975,1730,1754]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) anteriorly with pair of narrow, irregular longitudinal dark brown stripes, variably interrupted and thus forming pairs of approximately aligned maculae; lateral portions with irregular elongate dark brown stripe. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EC82F8CBFBC15C77" box="[947,1046,1802,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with pair of irregular longitudinal dark brown stripes on mediolateral portions; mesoscutum with anteromedian, longitudinal narrow dark brown stripe; pair of transverse, evanescent dark brown maculae anterior to scutoscutellar suture. Forewings (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B479C250EA7DF893FA465C3F" box="[1356,1425,1874,1898]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1420,700,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,700,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, apical left portion of pygofer, dorsal view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, styles and connective, dorsal view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216427/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B479C250EAB4F893FA465C3F" box="[1413,1425,1874,1898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) tanned-yellow with longitudinal veins pale yellow to white. 
<collectingCountry id="3D81A7C0B479C250EC74F8B7FCAA5CDB" box="[837,893,1910,1934]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings pale brown with veins dark brown. Face yellow with dark brown maculae. Frons with narrow dark brown stripe on dorsomedian portion; narrow dark brown stripes on muscle impressions. Clypeus with median, irregular dark brown stripe extending from epistomal suture and becoming evanescent ventrally. Lora with inner margin dark brown. Genae with inner margin dark brown; irregular dark brown stripe extending vertically from ventral margin of eye to lorum. Thoracic pleura yellow with dark brown stripes and maculae; lateral lobe of pronotum with two narrow, longitudinal dark brown stripes on anterodorsal portion, variably connected posteriorly. Legs yellow with variable dark brown areas. Thoracic sternum yellow with some dark brown areas. Abdomen dark brown with apical portion yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4529E750B47AC253EFF6FE8DFEA159D1" blockId="2.[151,1436,151,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Female genitalia (based on one 
<typeStatus id="9A2D59F2B47AC253ED75FE8DFD7D5A31" box="[580,682,332,356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">paratype</typeStatus>
). Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B47AC253EC6EFE8DFC715A31" box="[863,934,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,204,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[158,1428,193,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Female paratype: 8, abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; 9, pygofer, lateral view; 10, internal abdominal sternite VIII, dorsal view; 11, first valvula of ovipositor, apical portion and dorsal sculpturing in detail, lateral view; 12, second valvula of ovipositor, dorsal and apical portions in detail, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B47AC253ECA9FE8DFC715A31" box="[920,934,332,356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin with pair of short, narrowly rounded lateral processes; median portion with broad concavity with central emargination. Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B47AC253EA5EFEAEFF715AF9" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,204,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[158,1428,193,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Female paratype: 8, abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; 9, pygofer, lateral view; 10, internal abdominal sternite VIII, dorsal view; 11, first valvula of ovipositor, apical portion and dorsal sculpturing in detail, lateral view; 12, second valvula of ovipositor, dorsal and apical portions in detail, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B47AC253EFA6FE55FF715AF9" box="[151,166,404,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) moderately produced posteriorly in lateral view; apex narrowly rounded; surface with some short macrosetae along ventral margin and a few grouped near apex. Internal sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B47AC253ECF6FE76FBCF5A9A" box="[967,1048,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,204,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[158,1428,193,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Female paratype: 8, abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; 9, pygofer, lateral view; 10, internal abdominal sternite VIII, dorsal view; 11, first valvula of ovipositor, apical portion and dorsal sculpturing in detail, lateral view; 12, second valvula of ovipositor, dorsal and apical portions in detail, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B47AC253ECCAFE76FBCF5A9A" box="[1019,1048,439,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) without well-defined sclerites but with more sclerotized lateral areas. First valvulae (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B47AC253EDE0FE1DFCF65AA1" box="[721,801,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,204,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[158,1428,193,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Female paratype: 8, abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; 9, pygofer, lateral view; 10, internal abdominal sternite VIII, dorsal view; 11, first valvula of ovipositor, apical portion and dorsal sculpturing in detail, lateral view; 12, second valvula of ovipositor, dorsal and apical portions in detail, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B47AC253EC37FE1DFCF65AA1" box="[774,801,476,500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) of ovipositor slightly expanded on apical portion; apex acute; sculptured dorsally on about apical fourth, ventrally on about apical fifth; dorsal sculpturing sharply linear, subparallel and oblique. Second valvulae (
<figureCitation id="DDADFBD5B47AC253EDA0FDE5FD3F5969" box="[657,744,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,204,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[158,1428,193,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Sonesimia nessimiani, sp. nov. Female paratype: 8, abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; 9, pygofer, lateral view; 10, internal abdominal sternite VIII, dorsal view; 11, first valvula of ovipositor, apical portion and dorsal sculpturing in detail, lateral view; 12, second valvula of ovipositor, dorsal and apical portions in detail, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Fig. 
<number id="F35EF577B47AC253EDFAFDE5FD3F5969" box="[715,744,548,572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) with preapical prominence inconspicuous, rounded; apex subacute. Remaining morphological characteristics of female genitalia as in the generic description of Young (
<number id="F35EF577B47AC253EFAEFDADFF0B59D1" box="[159,220,620,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1977.0">1977</number>
: 
<number id="F35EF577B47AC253EFD6FDADFEBD59D1" box="[231,362,620,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1085.0" valueMax="1086.0" valueMin="1084.0">
<date id="3128C190B47AC253EFD6FDADFEBD59D1" box="[231,362,620,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1084" valueMax="1086">1084–1086</date>
</number>
).
</paragraph>
